# ----------------------------- MAN  ----------------------------------|
# 
# Sections:
#   1. SUBJECT: Everything needs a subject/title.
#      Ex: [INIT] Implement automated commit messages
#
#   ----- Everything below is optional -----
#   2. WHY: Explain the reason for this commit. Maybe, just because AI 
#      told so.
#   3. WHAT: Explain what(not how) makes this commit address why. What 
#      was wrong before, for what they work now. How should be in code.
#   4. Tickets: Provide links or keys to any relevant tickets.
#      Ex: 
#      - <JIRA> SHEBA-123, AW-456
#      - <SENTRY> 1122334455
#   5. References: Provide links to relevant so/github/other resources.
#      Long links can be broken, until some markdown is supported.
#      Ex:
#      - https://chris.beams.io/posts/git-commit/
#      - https://gist.github.com/zakkak/7e06725ebd1336bfebebe254de3de825
#   6. Co-authors: Who else worked on this commit, if you pair program.
#      Ex: Hasan Hafiz Pasha <pasha.startern@gmail.com>
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------|
#
# Tags: 
#   INIT     (initial commit for new feature/project)
#   ADD      (add something)
#   UPDATE   (update something)
#   FIX      (bug fix)
#   REFACTOR (refactoring code)
#   STYLE    (formatting, missing semi colon, etc; no logic change)
#   DOC      (changes to documentation)
#   TEST     (adding/updating tests; no production code change)
#   DEBUG    (debugging code/frameworks; no production code change)
#   HACK     (temporary fix to make things move forward)
#   WIP      (intermediate commits to keep patches reasonably sized)
#
# Note: Multiple tags can be combined, 
# [FIX][REFACTOR] Fix issue X with methodhandles
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------|
#
# Remember to:
#   * Capitalize the subject line.
#   * Use the imperative mood in the subject line.
#   * Do not end the subject line with a period.
#   * Separate subject from body with a blank line.
#   * Use the body to explain what and why vs. how.
#   * Use multiple lines with "-" for bullet points in body.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------|
